---
description: Disallow emojis and emoticons in backend and frontend code
globs: "**/*.py, **/*.html, **/*.js, **/*.css"
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Emojis in Code

- Do not use emojis or emoticon characters in any backend or frontend code.
- This includes:
  - Log messages
  - User-facing text in templates
  - Comments and documentation inside code files
- Use clear text instead of emojis. For example:
  - Use "HTTPS Enabled - Using SSL certificates" rather than prefixed lock icons.
  - Use "Warning: HTTP mode, camera may not work from remote devices" rather than warning symbols.

